        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 5:33PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 532 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Bridgeport, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Higdon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
